title: Discord bot
content:
import contextlib
import json
import time
from pathlib import Path
from urllib.error import HTTPError
from urllib.request import urlopen

from colorama import Fore
from discord_webhook import DiscordWebhook, DiscordEmbed


webhook = DiscordWebhook(url="WEBHOOK_URL")
SERVER_ADDRESS = "SERVER_IP:SERVER_PORT"

URL = f"http://{SERVER_ADDRESS}/JSON%7C"
buffer = Path(__file__).parent / "buffer.json"

print("Script Started!")
print("Developed by www.iiferedon.xyz")
print("Discord: iiferedon#1337")


def send_player_connected(player_name: str, colour: int, car_model: str, skin: str) -> None:
    """Send message informing about a connecting player."""
    embed = DiscordEmbed(title="Player connected", color=colour)
    embed.set_footer(text=' ')
    embed.set_timestamp()

    embed.add_embed_field(name="Player Name", value=player_name)
    embed.add_embed_field(name='Car', value=car_model)
    embed.add_embed_field(name='Skin', value=skin)

    webhook.add_embed(embed)
    webhook.execute()


def send_player_disconnected(player_name: str, colour: int):
    """Send message informing about a disconnecting player."""
    embed = DiscordEmbed(title="Player disconnected", description=f"{player_name} left", color=colour)

    embed.set_footer(text=' ')
    embed.set_timestamp()
    webhook.add_embed(embed)
    webhook.execute()


def main():
    while True:
        try:
            with contextlib.closing(urlopen(URL, timeout=5)) as response:
                json_data = response.read()
        except HTTPError:
            print(Fore.RED + "Error, server unavailable.")
            raise SystemExit()

        parsed = json.loads(json_data)

        if buffer.stat().st_size == 0:
            buffer.write_text(json_data, encoding='utf-8')

            print(Fore.GREEN +"Startup Buffer Initialized!")

        buffer_json = json.loads(buffer.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))

        for server_car, buffer_car in zip(parsed['Cars'], buffer_json['Cars']):
            if server_car['IsConnected'] and buffer_car['IsConnected']:
                print(f"{Fore.MAGENTA}Users in session")
            elif server_car['IsConnected'] and not buffer_car['IsConnected']:
                print(
                    f"{Fore.GREEN}JOINED GAME: Player: {server_car['DriverName']},"
                    f" is driving: {server_car['Model']},"
                    f" with skin: {server_car['Skin']}"
                )
                send_player_connected(
                    player_name=server_car['DriverName'],
                    colour=5_763_719,
                    car_model=server_car['Model'],
                    skin=server_car['Skin'],
                )
            elif not server_car['IsConnected'] and buffer_car['IsConnected']:
                print(
                    f"{Fore.GREEN}LEFT GAME: Player: {server_car['DriverName']}"
                )
                send_player_disconnected(
                    player_name=server_car['DriverName'],
                    colour=15_548_997,
                )

        buffer.write_text(json_data, encoding='utf-8')
        print(f"{Fore.BLUE}wrote to buffer\n..")
        time.sleep(2)


if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

-- Associer le moniteur et les tanks à leurs périphériques respectifs
local monitor = peripheral.wrap("top") -- Moniteur sur le côté "top"
local tanks = {
    peripheral.wrap("fluidTank_1"),
    peripheral.wrap("fluidTank_2"),
    peripheral.wrap("fluidTank_3"),
    peripheral.wrap("fluidTank_4")
}

monitor.clear()
monitor.setTextScale(1)

-- Noms manuels des liquides pour chaque tank
local fluidNames = {
    [1] = "Potion of Night Vision (3:00)",
    [2] = "Potion of Night Vision (8:00)",
    [3] = "Awkward Potion",
    [4] = "Water"
}

-- Fonction pour récupérer les informations d'un tank avec nom manuel
function getTankInfo(tank, index)
    local tankInfo = tank.getInfo()
    local fluidName = fluidNames[index] or "Unknown Fluid"
    local amount = tankInfo and tankInfo.amount or 0
    return fluidName, amount
end

-- Fonction pour afficher les informations sur l'Advanced Monitor
function displayTankInfo()
    for i, tank in ipairs(tanks) do
        local name, amount = getTankInfo(tank, i)
        local capacity = 432000  -- Capacité maximale fixe
        local percentage = (amount / capacity) * 100

        -- Afficher les informations du tank : contenu et capacité
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, (i - 1) * 3 + 1)  -- Espacement entre les lignes
        monitor.write(name)
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, (i - 1) * 3 + 2)
        monitor.write(amount .. " / " .. capacity .. " mB (" .. string.format("%.2f", percentage) .. "%)")
    end
end

-- Rafraîchir les informations toutes les secondes
while true do
    monitor.clear()
    displayTankInfo()
    sleep(1)
end

title: Football League
content:
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
    var stadiumCapacity, fanCount, sectorA, sectorB, sectorV, sectorG int
    fmt.Scanln(&stadiumCapacity)
    fmt.Scanln(&fanCount)
 
    var currentFanSector string
 
    for i := 0; i < fanCount; i++ {
        fmt.Scanln(&currentFanSector)
        switch currentFanSector {
        case "A":
            sectorA++
        case "B":
            sectorB++
        case "V":
            sectorV++
        case "G":
            sectorG++
        }
    }
 
    fmt.Printf("%.2f%%\n", float64(sectorA) / float64(fanCount) * 100)
    fmt.Printf("%.2f%%\n", float64(sectorB) / float64(fanCount) * 100)
    fmt.Printf("%.2f%%\n", float64(sectorV) / float64(fanCount) * 100)
    fmt.Printf("%.2f%%\n", float64(sectorG) / float64(fanCount) * 100)
    fmt.Printf("%.2f%%\n", float64(fanCount) / float64(stadiumCapacity) * 100)
}

title: Docker Compose 1Nodes Elastic
content:
services:
  setup:
    image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.15.2
    volumes:
      - certs:/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs
    user: "0"
    command: >
      bash -c '
        if [ x${ELASTIC_PASSWORD} == x ]; then
          echo "Set the ELASTIC_PASSWORD environment variable in the .env file";
          exit 1;
        elif [ x${KIBANA_PASSWORD} == x ]; then
          echo "Set the KIBANA_PASSWORD environment variable in the .env file";
          exit 1;
        fi;
        if [ ! -f config/certs/ca.zip ]; then
          echo "Creating CA";
          bin/elasticsearch-certutil ca --silent --pem -out config/certs/ca.zip;
          unzip config/certs/ca.zip -d config/certs;
        fi;
        if [ ! -f config/certs/certs.zip ]; then
          echo "Creating certs";
          echo -ne \
          "instances:\n"\
          "  - name: dedaleiro01\n"\
          "    dns:\n"\
          "      - dedaleiro01\n"\
          "      - localhost\n"\
          "    ip:\n"\
          "      - 127.0.0.1\n"\
          > config/certs/instances.yml;
          bin/elasticsearch-certutil cert --silent --pem -out config/certs/certs.zip --in config/certs/instances.yml --ca-cert config/certs/ca/ca.crt --ca-key config/certs/ca/ca.key;
          unzip config/certs/certs.zip -d config/certs;
        fi;
        echo "Setting file permissions"
        chown -R root:root config/certs;
        find . -type d -exec chmod 750 \{\} \;;
        find . -type f -exec chmod 640 \{\} \;;
        echo "Waiting for Elasticsearch availability";
        until curl -s --cacert config/certs/ca/ca.crt https://dedaleiro01:9200 | grep -q "missing authentication credentials"; do sleep 60; done;
        echo "Setting kibana_system password";
        until curl -s -X POST --cacert config/certs/ca/ca.crt -u "elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}" -H "Content-Type: application/json" https://dedaleiro01:9200/_security/user/kibana_system/_password -d "{\"password\":\"${KIBANA_PASSWORD}\"}" | grep -q "^{}"; do sleep 10; done;
        echo "All done!";
      '
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "[ -f config/certs/dedaleiro01/dedaleiro01.crt ]"]
      interval: 1s
      timeout: 20s
      retries: 120

  dedaleiro01:
    depends_on:
      setup:
        condition: service_healthy
    image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.15.2
    volumes:
      - certs:/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs
      - dedaleirodata01:/usr/share/elasticsearch/data
    ports:
      - ${ES_PORT}:9200
    environment:
      - node.name=dedaleiro01
      - cluster.name=${CLUSTER_NAME}
      - cluster.initial_master_nodes=dedaleiro01
      - ELASTIC_PASSWORD=${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}
      - bootstrap.memory_lock=true
      - xpack.security.enabled=true
      - xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled=true
      - xpack.security.http.ssl.key=certs/dedaleiro01/dedaleiro01.key
      - xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate=certs/dedaleiro01/dedaleiro01.crt
      - xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate_authorities=certs/ca/ca.crt
      - xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled=true
      - xpack.security.transport.ssl.key=certs/dedaleiro01/dedaleiro01.key
      - xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate=certs/dedaleiro01/dedaleiro01.crt
      - xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate_authorities=certs/ca/ca.crt
      - xpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode=certificate
      - xpack.license.self_generated.type=${LICENSE}
    mem_limit: ${MEM_LIMIT}
    ulimits:
      memlock:
        soft: -1
        hard: -1
    healthcheck:
      test:
        [
          "CMD-SHELL",
          "curl -s --cacert config/certs/ca/ca.crt https://localhost:9200 | grep -q 'missing authentication credentials'",
        ]
      interval: 10s
      timeout: 20s
      retries: 120

  kibana:
    depends_on:
      dedaleiro01:
        condition: service_healthy
    image: docker.elastic.co/kibana/kibana:8.15.2
    volumes:
      - certs:/usr/share/kibana/config/certs
      - kibanadata:/usr/share/kibana/data
    ports:
      - ${KIBANA_PORT}:5601
    environment:
      - SERVERNAME=kibana
      - ELASTICSEARCH_HOSTS=https://dedaleiro01:9200
      - ELASTICSEARCH_USERNAME=kibana_system
      - ELASTICSEARCH_PASSWORD=${KIBANA_PASSWORD}
      - ELASTICSEARCH_SSL_CERTIFICATEAUTHORITIES=config/certs/ca/ca.crt
    mem_limit: ${MEM_LIMIT}
    healthcheck:
      test:
        [
          "CMD-SHELL",
          "curl -s -I http://localhost:5601 | grep -q 'HTTP/1.1 302 Found'",
        ]
      interval: 10s
      timeout: 20s
      retries: 120

volumes:
  certs:
    driver: local
  dedaleirodata01:
    driver: local
  kibanadata:
    driver: local
